title: NYC Community Health Survey, 2007 (beta)
name: NYC Community Health Survey, 2007 (beta)
description:
CHS 2007 had 51 select survey measures, covering the following health topics: general physical and mental health; weight, exercise, nutrion; access to health care; blood pressure and cholesterol; cancer screening; cigarette smoking and alcohol; depression; asthma; HIV testing; sexual behavior and orientation; diabetes; vaccination; and environmental health.

PLEASE NOTE: Zeros should be interpreted as null values. Variables that have a restricted flag (i.e. DEPRES2_R = 1) represent estimates that should be interpreted with caution due to small sample size.  Validate all data against EpiQuery at http://www.nyc.gov/health/epiquery .
This data includes supplemental information necessary for correct interpretation, available in the attribute detail of this document.  

Provides United Hospital Fund boundaries and age-adjusted rates for a number of health topics covering the following health topics: general health status, health care access, cardiovascular health, diabetes, asthma, immunizations, mental health, smoking, second-hand smoke, obesity, commuting patterns, physical activity, cancer screening, HIV, sexual behavior, birth control, drug use, and domestic violence.

author.source: Bureau Epi Services, New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene
